The Recruitment Hive is a proud Equal Opportunity Employer. We recognise the value of diverse perspectives and experience and are committed to an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected for who they are. We encourage people with disability, indigenous, veterans and people of all backgrounds and abilities to express their interest in this role.

Who we are:    
Funds SA is a South Australian Government Corporation that invests and manages over AUD$50 billion on behalf of South Australian public-sector superannuation funds and approved public authorities.

Funds SA’s primary aim is to build prosperity for South Australians through the investment performance they generate for their clients. Our organisational expertise, deep investment partnerships, and ‘manager of managers’ approach drive a pursuit of future financial prosperity through global market reach. This, combined with our team’s experience, sophisticated investment solutions and agility, enable us to navigate the continually evolving financial landscape.

Funds SA prides itself on strong leadership driving a values led, supportive culture, focused on providing opportunities to learn, grow, and work with great people.

Key Responsibilities

Support the development and implementation of the responsible investment strategy and initiatives of the organisation;
Support asset class teams with embedding responsible investment practices;
Support the implementation of key responsible investment initiatives, including Funds SA’s approach to managing the risks of climate change and undertaking investment ESG due diligence;
Contribute to stewardship activities, including proxy voting activities;
Support management and monitoring of the Socially Responsible Investment (SRI) option;
Undertake and contribute to research on responsible investment opportunities, trends and themes;
Contribute to internal and external reports for relevant stakeholders (i.e. PRI, Investment Committee and the Board)
Collaborate with different stakeholders on various projects as needed to achieve business objectives.
Key Skills, Knowledge and Experience:

Tertiary qualifications in science, engineering, finance, economics, mathematics or similar relevant fields;
Knowledge and experience working within ESG / responsible investment or investment management with exposure to responsible investment activities;
Strong analytical and numerical skills and ability to interpret and analyse scientific, economic, and financial information;
Understanding and knowledge of relevant legislative, regulatory, governance procedures and practices relating to Funds SA’s activities;
Ability to work with a diverse range of internal and external stakeholders;
Highly self-motivated, professional and adaptable to change; AND
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills and organisational skills.
Funds SA values diversity and is an equal opportunity employer.

This is an exceptional opportunity for an aspiring investment performance professional to grow their career in a leading investor, which provides genuine professional development opportunities within a collaborative and high-performance culture.

